text: Eintracht Frankfurt is a German women's association football team that represents Frankfurt and plays in the Frauen Bundesliga. The team was called 1. FFC Frankfurt until 2020. The team is the most successful German team, both in the league and in Europe. Frankfurt has won 7 Bundesliga titles, 4 UEFA Women's Champions League titles and 9 DFB-Pokal titles. Some notable players include Birgit Prinz, Fatmire Alushi, Melanie Behringer, Célia Šašić and Simone Laudehr. == Record == === Bundesliga === Season League Position 1998–99 Bundesliga 1st 1999–00 Bundesliga 2nd 2000–01 Bundesliga 1st 2001–02 Bundesliga 1st 2002–03 Bundesliga 1st 2003–04 Bundesliga 2nd 2004–05 Bundesliga 1st 2005–06 Bundesliga 3rd 2006–07 Bundesliga 1st 2007–08 Bundesliga 1st 2008–09 Bundesliga 4th 2009–10 Bundesliga 3rd 2010–11 Bundesliga 2nd 2011–12 Bundesliga 3rd 2012–13 Bundesliga 3rd 2013–14 Bundesliga 2nd 2014–15 Bundesliga 3rd 2015–16 Bundesliga 3rd 2016–17 Bundesliga 5th 2017–18 Bundesliga 6th 2018–19 Bundesliga 5th 2019–20 Bundesliga 6th 2020–21 Bundesliga 6th 2021–22 Bundesliga 3rd 2022–23 Bundesliga 3rd Bundesliga Bundesliga Bundesliga Bundesliga Bundesliga == References == == Other websites == * 1.
